---
import Layout from "../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Header from "../components/Header.astro";
import Footer from "../components/Footer.astro";
---

<Layout title="Felipe Franco We Are Dust Project" />

<main>
    <section class="sm:h-screen w-screen">
        <Header />
        <div class="sm:pr-[25%] text-center sm:text-right">
            <h1>Baptism</h1>
            <p>2023</p>
        </div>

        <div
            class="w-screen flex justify-center lg:h-[500px] sm:h-[400px] h-[300px] max-w-[1200px] m-auto sm:my-20 my-10"
        >
            <iframe
                class="w-[90%]"
                src="https://www.youtube.com/embed/i1SGXNqe9RE?si=Y2yGeQRohBoUcLIv"
                title="YouTube video player"
                frameborder="0"
                allow="accelerometer; autoplay; clipboard-write; encrypted-media; gyroscope; picture-in-picture; web-share"
                referrerpolicy="strict-origin-when-cross-origin"
                allowfullscreen></iframe>
        </div>

        <div class="w-screen hidden sm:flex justify-center animate-bounce">
            <a href="#next4">
                <img
                    class="w-[30px] cursor-pointer"
                    src="data:image/png;base64,"
                />
            </a>
        </div>
    </section>

    <section id="next4">
        <p
            class="w-[90%] max-w-[700px] m-auto my-28 py-10 border-y-[1px] border-solid border-[#b4b4b4c0] text-[12px] text-pretty"
        >
        Standing under a stream seems to be a questionable, unhygienic and reprehensible act, a ridiculous and senseless action. 
        From below, we see water falling, we anxiously dodge it as we walk down the street, as if it were an attack coming from the architecture. 
        Seeking to have an affective approach with the building, I decide to perform a patient action, and wait under a stream that falls from my home. 
        Without shame, but with fear, I expose my body; which, expectant, fragile and patient, waits to be bathed by the water that purifies my house, and then, travels the slope to its destination. 
        Standing becomes a gesture of recognition of the space, of the building, of the home, a baptism coming from the darkened water that the architecture nonchalantly releases.
        </p>
    </section>

    <Footer />
</main>
